Chord Naming

Streamlined Naming System
Reworked chord suffix logic:

    Minor chords are consistently labeled as m

    Major chords are labeled as Maj


    Examples: Cm, CMaj, Cm7, CMaj7, CmM7

Improved Augmented / Diminished Detection

    Refined recognition of E–Ab–C–G: now displayed as Eaug(#9) instead of E(add#5,#9)

    Automatically suppresses redundant #5 or b5 markings in augmented/diminished chords

Alt Label Optimization

    Chords such as 7#9 no longer force an additional alt label when altered tensions are already explicitly defined

Added 5 Chord Support

    Root + perfect fifth is now explicitly displayed as a 5 chord (power chord)

Core Engine Fixes
Two-Note / Interval Analysis

    Two-note input now displays the interval name in real time (e.g., Major 3rd, Perfect 4th)

    Fixed C–D–G being incorrectly detected as Csus2add9

        Now correctly identified as Csus2

        Adds inversion hint: Gsus4/C

Omission & Inversion Logic Refactor

    Fixed ambiguous detection for C–Eb–F

        Now prioritizes Cmadd11(no5)

        Also suggests F7(no3)

    Adjusted preference for C–Eb–G–Ab

        Now recognized as Cm(b13)

        Provides AbM7/C as inversion reference

Extended Tension Enhancements

11 / 13 Series

    Fixed incomplete detection for C–Eb–G–D–F

        Now correctly recognized as Cmadd9,11

#11 Series

    Fixed failure to detect #11 in C–E–F#–B

        CM7(#11) is now recognized even without the fifth

b13 / Alt Series

    Added support for 7(b13) and 7(b9,b13) including versions with the fifth

    Expanded detection for common jazz alterations: 7(#5,#9) and 7alt

    Added recognition for 7(#9) including full five-note voicings

b5 Series

    Added full support for: Maj7b5, 7b5, 9b5, 13b5

UI & Interaction

Sharp / Flat Toggle

    Added global # / b toggle

    Switch between sharp-based or flat-based note naming instantly

Improved Inversion Display

    Refined first inversion handling for minor chords

        Avoids misleading labels such as D#M6, and instead prioritizes root-related interpretation

    Added more inversion and enharmonic references in the secondary suggestion line

        Example: Gsus now also references related Csus structures

Changelog:

    Sustain Pedal Support: Added full support for MIDI CC 64 (Sustain Pedal).

    Sticky Mode: Introduced a new Freeze/Sticky mode. When enabled, the display will hold the last detected chord after the MIDI signal ceases.

    Chord Visualization: Optimized the display for dim7 and dim7(b13) chords.

    Enhanced Detection: Chords consisting of E3,G#3,C4,E4,G#4,A#4, and D#5 will now be correctly identified and displayed as EMaj7(b5 b13).

    UI Refinement: Redesigned the visual style of the # / b (Sharp/Flat) toggle in the top-right corner.

    Layout Optimization: Improved the typography and spatial arrangement of the Theme Menu.

    Algorithm & Stability: Enhanced the core recognition algorithm and fixed several known bugs.

Added chord degree display mode, allowing switching between Roman numerals and Arabic numerals.

Chord degree display mode now supports specifying the current key.

Redesigned the menu style.

Improved the theme system: foreground and background colors can now be customized.

Made all plugin parameters persistent.

Fixed unresponsive buttons and theme display issues in Cubase.

Algorithm optimizations and other bug fixes.

Grand Staff View: MIDI Lens can now display your playing as live sheet music. Notes are rendered in real time on both the treble and bass clef as you play.

Keyboard Degree Labels: In Degree Display Mode, scale degree numbers based on the selected key are now shown above the piano keyboard.

Added a new menu option: "Show Scale Degrees Above Keyboard in Default Mode". When enabled, degree labels appear above each key even when the chord display is in standard (non-degree) mode.

The plugin window is now resizable.

Improved the visual style of hover tooltips.

Refined the naming of sus chords. Inversion display for seventh and ninth chords is now more accurate.

Significant algorithm improvements, code cleanup, and various rendering refinements.
